Date: Mon, 1 Jun 1998 00:56:48 -0400 (EDT)
From: Jonathan Mayer <jmayer@hsph.harvard.edu>

I'm curious why this [Ron St. John's comments regarding needed skills in
treating dengue hemorrhagic fever/dengue shock syndrome cases. - Mod.CHC
is the case, since my impression is that the best that can be done
clinically for dengue are non-specific supportive measures, and that if the
person progresses to DIC, that there is little that can be done that isn't
done for DIC regardless of the etiology.
--
Jonathan D. Mayer, Ph.D.
Harvard School of Public Health
Department of Population and International Health
665 Huntington Ave. 1-11
Boston MA 02115
TEL: (617)-432-1237
